properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 11 at 12:10PM CST until January 12 at 6:00AM CST by NWS Green Bay WI
properties.description:
...WINTER WEATHER WILL IMPACT TRAVEL THIS WEEKEND...

.Another round of snow will arrive late this afternoon and early
evening, bringing total snowfall accumulations of 2 to 5 inches,
heaviest along the lakeshore. Along with the snowfall,
considerable blowing and drifting snow will occur, especially from
the Fox Valley to the lakeshore counties. The worst conditions
will occur along the lakeshore areas, where the highest snowfall
totals are expected, and north to northeast winds will gust to 35
to 40 mph. Travel conditions will be significantly impacted.

* WHAT...Snow and blowing snow expected. Total snow accumulations
of up to two inches. Winds gusting as high as 40 mph.

* WHERE...Door County.

* WHEN...From 6 PM this evening to 6 AM CST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. Areas of blowing and
drifting snow could significantly reduce visibility. Gusty
winds could bring down tree branches, resulting in localized
power outages.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 6 PM THIS EVENING TO 6 AM CST SUNDAY
